definitions.definition: A specialized organ constructed of thick muscular walls found in the digestive tract of some animals, including archosaurs (including crocodilians and birds ), earthworms , some gastropods , some fish , and some crustaceans , and used for grinding up food, often aided by particles of stone or grit.
